<br>
Season 7, Episode 1<br>
The Journey Home<br>
A young runaway girl Jacinna joins Gabrielle after she returns to Greece and saves the girls village from a mean warlord. The village leaders thank her and tell her that the warlord visits all the local towns for food and money. Gabrielle agrees to visit the other towns. She tries to convince Jacinna to go home, but the young girl insists on travelling with her. Gabrielle sits by a night campfire and Jacinna gives her a funny look when she whispers to somebody not there named Xena about advice. Gabrielle looks sad so Jacinna reads her a story. Gabrielle is pleased to learn Jacinna wants to be a bard. Gabrielle saves another village from the warlord the next day. Gabrielle asks Jacinna to go home to tell everyone to fight. She doesnt think they will, but Gabrielle says they must be brave. When Jacinna returns home, her mother hugs her. She was worried about her and Jacinna feels sorry for that. The next day the warlord's army arrives and he finds people ready to fight. The villagers fight off the mean warlord's men. Gabrielle fights the warlord and uses her chakram to cut his belt. His pants fall down. Everyone sees his polka-dot underwear and they all laugh. The mean warlord is embarrased and runs away for good. Gabrielle tells Jacinna she must stay, the young girl will miss her family if she leaves. Jacinna agrees. Gabrielle tells her to keep writing and gives her a scroll titled Sins of the Past. Gabrielle rides off while Jacinna waves goodbye.          <br>
<br>
Season 7, Episode 2<br>
Sisters<br>
Gabrielle returns to the Amazons. Eve is also there to ask Amazon forgiveness. Eve sees Xena's horse and asks of her mother. Gabrielle tells her what happened and everyone is sad. Later that night, Varia announces to the Amazons that Eve will be given a second chance, but she must pass three tests. Amazon sister Selthe still doesnt like Eve much but she stays quiet. Eve's first test is to hunt for food with a bow and arrow. Gabrielle goes with her. Eve sees a deer by a cliff but she can't shoot the defenseless animal. It runs away. Gabrielle tells Eve to look down the cliff. Another deer fell days ago and is no longer alive. They can take that deer instead and leave the other in peace. Eve's second test is to go into a Roman camp and do good. Selthe sneaks around in the forest and yells out so Eve and Gabrielle are caught. A Roman Commander questions them, but his leg hurts and he sits down. Eve offers some healing medicine and he thanks her. He lets them go free. Eve's final test is to offer the council something important. Eve decides to write scrolls of the Amazons' history. The council likes that idea but Selthe speaks out. She wants Eve gone. Eve agrees to leave if it is best. Varia says that Eve willing to sacrifice being an Amazon for the greater good shows she is forgiven. Varia tells Selthe she is the one to leave. Selthe must go and learn to forgive others. The Amazons have a party that night to celebrate their new sister Eve. <br>
      <br>
Season 7, Episode 3<br>
Caste Down<br>
Varia prepares for a trip to Northern Amazon lands to gather historical records. Eve is busy with her studies so Gabrielle volunteers to go with her. As they ride by horse, Gabrielle tells flashbacks of Xena's time with Borias and Alti, and her own near death fight with Alti in the afterlife. Varia says each tribe has a storyteller. They camp for the night intending to meet Chi'ah, guardian of the tree amber, the next day. On their way to the cave of amber, wild men, Samnite nomads attack them. Gabrielle and Varia fight them off but Gabrielle gets hurt. In the cave, Chi'ah greets them. The Samnite nomads attack again and Varia and Gabrielle win again. Chi'ah casts a spell that hides the cave from them. She tells the two young Amazons flashbacks of Alti's blame for all this. Her spells and attempts to gain the nomad's rage and power were forbidden. Queen Cyane's removed her from the tribe and Alti got her revenge by learning of soul power in the Book of the Atma. Queen Cyane ordered Chi'ah hidden in the caves to watch over it and all other items of importance. Varia leaves the caves and leads the nomads away. Chi'ah gives Gabrielle the Book of the Atma. She makes her promise her tribe's protector will guard it well. Chi'ah remains in the caves out of loyalty to her tribe. Gabrielle later meets with Varia who lost the nomads. Gabrielle shows her the Book. Varia promises to honor Amazon traditions. Eve will learn and protect the Book of the Atma well. <br>
      <br>
Season 7, Episode 4<br>
Tribe of the Sai<br>
Gabrielle fights criminals attacking a village market, but one of her sais in broken during the battle. The blacksmith offers her a free sword, but she takes a staff instead. She feels sad about her broken sai until someone tells her of a fabled lost Amazon tribe to the east. The Tribe of the Sai. Gabrielle rides out to find the tribe. The criminals follow her but she looses them. Down the path Gabrielle meets a girl chased by two wild Amazons with sais. They see Gabrielle's weapon and run away. The girl thanks her. She is an Amazon who treated a man with kindness, but her tribe look down on men. Gabrielle thinks that's wrong and agrees to take her back home. Warrior women meet them outside the hidden tribe. The girl is taken away and Gabrielle meets the Queen. She says Gabrielle's tribes have grown weak and peaceful. Gabrielle must leave, without her sais. As Gabrielle argues that men can be good, the criminals attack the tribe. The Amazons win their fight with the men. The Queen is impressed with Gabrielle's fighting skills, but her staff is too peaceful. Gabrielle suggests she should keep her mind open to new ways. Later that night, the girl takes part in a ceremonial fight to regain her place in the tribe. She uses some of Gabrielle's moves and wins. The girl is forgiven and allowed back in the tribe. She gives Gabrielle her fighting sais as a present. The Queen tells Gabrielle she is welcomed to return as an honorary member to the tribe. <br>
<br>
Season 7, Episode 5<br>
The Old Grey Mare<br>
A masked theif breaks into a home to steal jewels but he is caught by the owner, old Autolycus. A knock on the door distracts him and the thief gets away. Gabrielle has been looking for a lost gold pillow for a nearby king. Autolycus says he stole it fair and square but now its been stolen from him. Autolycus is a man of class now, he runs a respectable theives school. Only problem he is one of his students has just robbed him. The next day he saddles up his old mare horse that always runs off from him. Gabrielle goes in town and spots the man in a bar. She fights him but he gets away. She Xena-pinches one guy and he tells her where the student went. Autolycus insists on going with her. Nobody takes his King of Theives title. His horse makes a sound like a laugh and runs off again. Gabrielle and Autolycus find the theif but he gets away again. They chase him all the way to the king's apple orchard. Gabrielle fights the student and finally wins. Autolycus picks up the gold pillow to take credit but the king arrives and thanks his old horse instead. He grants the horse all the apples she can eat. Autolycus mumbles of a gold reward but his mare horse looks at him all innocent. He says apples are ok and his horse runs off to eat some red apples. Gabrielle smiles and offers him some gold for the trip back home. Autolycus thanks her but he already stole her gold anyway. She shakes her head with a smile and they both eat an apple. <br>
<br>
Season 7, Episode 6<br>
Faith...Hope...Love<br>
While walking through the forest Gabrielle is approached by two men asking for help. She follows them and finds the place burned to ashes. The people are afraid of a young girl responsible. Gabrielle is uneasily reminded of her daughter. The next day village men from the village take up swords to find the girl. Gabrielle joins them. She splits from the group when she sees some child's clothes in a tree. Men yell from a distance and she runs to find them surround a young girl. Gabrielle picks up the girl and quickly runs to safety. The village leader thinks Gabrielle may be evil too. Gabrielle tries to comfort the quiet girl who says her mother died some time ago. Her father is a mean god, but he gives her powers to move things and make fires. Gabrielle seems certain of who she is and promises to protect her. Some of the villagers find Gabrielle and the girl. Gabrielle tries to fight them off but they are captured. They plan to burn Gabrielle and the girl, but the mean god arrives and winds start to pick up villagers and toss them around. Gabrielle frees herself. She fights the wind god but can not win, so she throws her chakram at a tree that falls on him. The wind god laughs and disappears. Gabrielle tells the villagers being scared of the girl and treating her mean started their problems. The villagers feel sorry for that. Gabrielle thinks about her daughter once more and offers to take the child with her. The girl smiles and goes with Gabrielle.  <br>
<br>
Season 7, Episode 7<br>
Peace and War<br>
Ares tells some villagers that they will worship him or be punished. Eve is there and tells him to stop. As Gabrielle and the girl enter the town, she tells Gabrielle the wind in the trees means her father is not far behind. He is still mad at Gabrielle. She sees Ares prepared to kill Eve and runs to stop him. They fight and Ares asks about Xena. Gabrielle tells him what happened and he blames her peaceful ways. Gabrielle, Eve and the girl go to the village Elisian school. The Priestess would be happy to take the girl. Eve worries about Ares. He has been building a big army. Gabrielle goes out to find him and the wind god appears. He attacks her and almost wins but Ares appears and says if anyone is going to get Gabrielle it is him. The wind god leaves. Ares tells Gabrielle that Xena could have won that fight. She asks why he is building an army. Ares smiles and disappears. When Gabrielle returns the girl says she doesnt want her powers if they will make her mean. Gabrielle hugs her and tells her not to worry. Ares returns the next day with his army. Gabrielle and the towns people are ready to fight. As a show of peace, Ares will spare the town if someone will sacrifice their life. He grabs the girl as his choice, but the wind god appears. Everyone runs for protection. The Priestess says the girl will be safe in the school. Eli's powers will protect them. Gabrielle says goodbye and leaves as Ares and the mean wind god continue to fight. <br>
      <br>
Season 7, Episode 8<br>
Wild Wolf<br>
Gabrielle's travels take her north into snow covered lands to a fort town. The king and queen are saddened at the loss of their son. The little boy went into the forest and he is lost. Gabrielle volunteers to search but the prince objects to a woman doing the job. The next morning Gabrielle wakes up to the horns of the prince's horses as they go out on a wolf hunt. Gabrielle finds little luck in her search until she stops by a stream for water. A wild boy drinks water and runs when he hears the prince's horn. The prince is mad Gabrielle ruined his chase. He secretly tells two guards to follow her. That night Gabrielle makes a campfire. She knows the boy is watching so she cooks some food. He approaches and sits down but doesnt speak. A wolf approaches the boy and lies down beside him. The two guards attack but Gabrielle and the boy win the fight. She thinks it strange the boy fights so well and the wolf prefers to rest and study her. A female wolf approaches the campfire and goes up to the boy. Gabrielle has her answer. Gabrielle the boy and two wolves return to town but the prince meets them. He fights Gabrielle and she wins. Gabrielle tells the king and queen the older prince and guard tried to harm the boy, the young prince, so the wolf somehow switched with him to protect him. The wolf switches bodies with the boy who hugs his mother. The older prince and guard are arrested. Everyone watches as the boy hugs the wolf goodbye. <br>
<br>
Season 7, Episode 9<br>
Faitve<br>
Gabrielle wakes from a dream of Xena trying to tell her something. Varia tells her its a vision. She must go to speak with the shamaness Faitve. Gabrielle travels for days until she reaches Faitve's hut in the dark, scary swamp.Gabrielle tells her of troubled dreams and her adventures with Xena. Faitve says she will make contact that night. By the fire, Faitve calls on the Xena's spirit to appear. Gabrielle and Xena share a smile but the appearance is lost. Faitve will need something of Xena's to make the calling stronger. Gabrielle gives her the chakram. That night while Gabrielle sleeps Faitve calls on Xena who is not happy with her. Xena knows the shamaness is a stealer of souls but she is captured by Faitve's magic. The next morning Gabrielle is told to make a spiritual journey in the swamps. Gabrielle walks for some time but she meets a crocodile. She gave her chakram to Faitve but to her surprise her sais are missing too. Gabrielle climbs a big tree for safety. Gabrielle goes back to demand answers but she is hit with a sleep dart. That night Faitve uses the chakram and sais to call upon Xena and Gabrielle's souls. She wants to own both. Faitve puts herself to sleep to fight them in the spirit world. Faitve is powerful but no match for Xena. Xena defeats her. Gabrielle asks about Faitve and Xena says the spirit world has her now. They are both sad as Xena must still stay behind. They share a hug and Gabrielle wakes up alone. <br>
<br>
Season 7, Episode 10<br>
Expedition<br>
A small boat meets the underwater research ship Mellosia to deliver Allison. Her aunt Lynda, the ship's captain, greets her. Lynda agreed to her niece's visit upon learning of her mother's untimely death. Allison is led to a room as the sonar expert informs Lynda the site has been found. At dinner Lynda tells the crew the salvage will be explored despite an approaching storm. That night Allison wakes to the sound of an argument. She sneaks out on the deck and sees the sonar expert fall overboard. Lynda calls for help but Allison is suspicious. Unfortunately the man is lost to the sea. Lynda asks her niece to travel in the diving bell with her the next day. Allison agrees. On the ocean floor they find a lost statue shaped like a woman. Lynda says it is of an ancient Amazon goddess named Velasca. Allison mentions her mother's studies of the woman as evil in myth and Lynda gives her a cold look. Lynda knows her niece saw the sonar expert killed. He tried to stop Lynda's research just like Allison's mother. Allison realizes what that means and she fights her aunt to escape. Lightning from the storm strikes the diving bell wires and it sinks to the bottom. Allison manages to get out with the diving mask at the last second. She swims back up to the ship. Lynda is left buried alive under tons of ocean water as her beside the remains of her ancestor Velasca buried alive under tons of lava ages ago. <br>
<br>
Season 7, Episode 11<br>
Secret Passage<br>
Far from the lands of Greece, Gabrielle battles with tavern criminals along the coast of Gaul. Authorities soon arrive but its clear they favor the criminals who pay generous bribes. Gabrielle runs and hides eventually seeking passage on a ship which sets sail for Egypt. Just as she begins to enjoy the voyage she sees another passenger, the dark Amazon Selthe. Gabrielle makes friends with many of the crew and passengers during the trip. Rumors grow that the ship travels well outside normal routes. On a night where the captain is on deck alone, Gabrielle asks him about that. He tells her the world is not flat and he will find a secret passage to India. A huge rope and hook swing almost hitting them both. Gabrielle suspects Selthe. Gabrielle searches the dark supply room and sees a large volcanic rock. To her surprise it is not a statue but an old enemy trapped in cooled lava. Velasca. Selthe and some men capture Gabrielle and the Captain. Selthe tells the crew the captain's plan to go off the edge of the world and they side with her. She takes Gabrielle to the rock and demands an Amazon spell to release the goddess Velasca. Selthe wins a fight with Gabrielle and starts the release chant. Gabrielle sees the fuels of ship's lamp oil and starts a fire. Crew and passengers escape the ship in small boats. The Captain asks why she would destroy his ship. Gabrielle assures him it was too great a risk for Velasca to return. Selthe is not found. <br>
<br>
Season 7, Episode 12<br>
The Burning Sand<br>
Gabrielle helps an Egyptian warrior named Imhatep as he fights desert theives. After they win the battle, she joins his people's crossing of the desert to claim their new royal city. Imhatep is a royal guard. He tells her that his people are turning to the new belief of a single god. Gabrielle shares her thoughts of Eli's god. They both agree their gods sound the same. Imhatep is ordered to the front of the caravan to protect Pharoah. Gabrielle follows and finds a great battle between guards and a Djinn. Djinn warns them all to turn back to their home and their worship of many gods. Pharoah refuses to listen and orders some guards to visit a nearby tomb as the others continue. Inside the tomb, Gabrielle reads the ancient text of how the desert was once green before the evil Djinn appeared. There was a great Thracian army send to defeat him in a holy crusade. Gabrielle recognizes a marking like one Najara once wore. She wonders how Najara ever ended up serving such an evil master. The Djinn attacks. Gabrielle and Imhatep barely escape to warn the hundreds of villagers and Pharoah. The Djinn has set a trap for them all. Magical sand tigers rise from the ground to attack the people. Pharoahs army fights bravely but can not win. Djinn makes Pharoah insane. Gabrielle uses the Xena-pinch to stop him. Holy Nile water stops the sand tigers and Djinn. Imhatep says Pharoah will get better. He thanks Gabrielle for helping his people to safety.<br>
<br>
Season 7, Episode 13<br>
Reshauven Falls<br>
Gabrielle's visit to the mystical kingdom of Reshauven is interrupted by attacking bird men. She runs to nearby waterfalls where a girl's flute makes them go away. Casandra recognizes Gabrielle. Her mother was Tara. She has heard many tales of Xena and Gabrielle. Bird men dont like waterfalls so they are safe. Casandra tells her Reshauven is in danger. There are attacks all the time. They walk through the magical waterfalls and find a great castle city hidden by magic. Casandra's flute keeps the bird men away but only she knows how to play it so travel is not safe. If they could make more, everyone could learn to play and be safe. Gabrielle and Casandra travel to find flute wood. Bird men try to attack but the flute keeps them away. At night the bird men leader swoops down and kidnaps Casandra to the flute tree. He plans to burn the tree with her tied to it. Gabrielle follows after her but she is attacked. She fights well but when she whistles the Xena song the bird men leave. She has an idea and races back to the waterfalls. The bird men leader ties Casandra to the flute tree. He prepares to start a fire but his bird men say the people are attacking. All the people are whistling the Xena song. Everyone fights. The bird men leader tries to attack Gabrielle but Casandra hits him on the head with her flute. Reshauven is saved. Everyone is happy. Casandra says Gabrielle is always welcome to visit her people.<br>
<br>
Season 7, Episode 14<br>
Chocolate Drops<br>
Aphrodite visits as Gabrielle tells a bed time story to Jacinna. Once upon a time there was a mean woman named Aphy dressed in pink who liked to drop chocolate on people's heads for fun. Aphrodite asks her about that name but Gabrielle just smiles. Two warriors came to save the people. Eva who had a big head and Vari who had rabbit teeth. Eva and Vari fought all the time. Aphy dropped chocolate on both their heads and disappeared laughing. Aphrodite asked why Aphy sounded alot like her but Gabrielle just smiled. Aphy kidnapped Jaci a young innocent girl. She was going to ruin Jaci's teeth with too much sweets. When Eva and Vari were not fighting they made their way up to Aphy's mountain secret cave. Aphrodite said she doesnt like caves they hide her beauty. Jacinna asked if they had any chocolate to eat. Eva and Vari found Aphy and there was a big fight. Aphy put a carrot on Vari's big teeth and made a chocolate river that took them both away. Jaci tricked her into falling into the chocolate. Aphy ate all the chocolate and got sick. Aphy learned that too much sweets is a bad thing. Jacinna learned that Gabrielle forgot to buy chocolate explaining the reason for the story. Aphrodite learned chocolate doesnt go well with pink dresses unless you color it pink. Gabrielle learned to not tell that story again when she woke later that night to a piece of chocolate dropped on her head and Aphrodite's smile. <br>
<br>
Season 7, Episode 15<br>
Of Lesser Gods<br>
A forest goddess asks her people not to fight the Romans but they go anyway. Gabrielle travels through the forest and hears a great battle. She helps the forest people to escape. To her surprise Virgil is there too. They hug and share stories around a campfire. The Romans want the forest for new cities. The Roman general thinks the goddess is weak. He will attack soon. Gabrielle meets the goddess. Her people should run but they will defend her. Gabrielle tells the tale of many gods who fell after the Twilight. The goddess knows about Xena but she is not mad. She thanks Gabrielle and Virgil for their help. Gabrielle and Virgil find the people in a valley trapped on both sides. The Romans attack. Many of the people are captured including Virgil but Gabrielle leads the others to safety. The goddess blames herself. Her gods aided the India people and have not been seen since. It is an uncertain age for gods. Gabrielle tells her she is alot like Artemis. The goddess asks that Gabrielle take her people to peaceful gods if something happens. Virgil defends a family from Roman guards and is beaten up. As a guard gets ready to put a sword to him, Gabrielle and the others attack. The fight goes well until more guards surround the people. The goddess appears. She sacrifices herself and disappears with all the Romans. A great amount of food is left in her place. Gabrielle understands. Sadly with new supplies she leads the people to a new land.    <br>
<br>
Season 7, Episode 16<br>
Best Friends<br>
Gabrielle meets Jacinna who is on her way to relatives. She is pleased to learn Jacinna wants to go to the Bards Academy. Jacinna wants to travel with Gabrielle a few days to learn her writing style and hear about Xena. They spend the next few days camping and fishing talking about Xena's adventures. Gabrielle throws the chakram for show. She hasnt learned the flips yet but she is trying. Gabrielle tells her all about Joxer, Callisto, Ares and Aphrodite. Jacinna still visits Aphrodite. The next day Jacinna tries to catch a rabbit for lunch and Gabrielle mentions the mean rabbit she once fought. Jacinna reads another of her scrolls. Gabrielle can see she is very talented. She will do very well at the Academy. When they stop by a small village for supplies, Gabrielle wins a fight with three bandits. She tells Jacinna of the many fights she and Xena were in. Sometimes Xena fought with anything: fish, frying pans, and bread. Gabrielle takes Jacinna's walking staff and shows her how to use it as a weapon. When Jacinna asks why she stopped writing, Gabrielle said she still does sometimes, but she is an Amazon and warrior too. She talks about all the Amazon friends she knew. And she talks about Aphrodite's enchanted scroll and her play scroll. After a week of travelling together, Gabrielle and Jacinna Jacinna says she has to go back home. Gabrielle gives her a hug and enough gold dinars so Jacinna's dreams of the Academy will come true. <br>
<br>
Season 7, Episode 17<br>
Nobody's Fool<br>
Virgil sneaks behind trees to see villagers grouped together by an army led by Salmaeus the Mighty. He is dressed exactly like Joxer. Before anyone is harmed, Virgil runs and fights some soldiers. Salmaeus orders his capture and the villagers are released. Virgil escapes. Gabrielle's visit with Jacinna after a week at the Academy is interrupted by Virgil needing help. Gabrielle and Virgil win a fight with Salmaeus' men. Virgil leads them to a now rich blacksmith making dozens of Joxer armors. He sais Salmaeus is nutty but the money still spends good. Virgil and Gabrielle dress up like Joxer to sneak into camp. They are surprized to see many dozen soldiers all dressed like Joxer. Jacinna doesnt listen to Gabrielle to stay behind. She is captured by Salmaeus' second man Bryian. While Virgil and Gabrielle plan her rescue, Jacinna and Bryian talk alot and an interest is definitely there. Too bad Salmaeus says. Jacinna is taken away to be done away with despite Bryian's protests. Virgil has a plan. He goes back to the blacksmith and asks to borrow a few Joxer armors to advertise. The man agrees. Gabrielle and Virgil get the villages to dress up and they all mix in with Salmaeus' soldiers. A fight starts. Bryian goes to rescue Jacinna but Salmaeus defeats him. Gabrielle rescues Bryian by hitting Salmaeus' pointy helmet down on his head. Salmaeus sees stars and falls down. Virgil says he is keeping one Joxer armor to remember his dad.<br>
<br>
Season 7, Episode 18<br>
Empress<br>
The sorceress Venshue visits her sister Queen Tianu. Venshue's practice in black arts gave her a vision. The return of Tataka but they need her chosen host. Venshue mentions the name Gabrielle. Gabrielle continues her brief vacation in India to find The Blue Scroll she lost. She meets some people who learned of Eve's Elisian teachings. Borshi was a favored student of Eve. He shows her the main city but they are attacked by Tianu's guards. Gabrielle is taken to the palace where Venshue tells her the plan. Gabrielle will allow the joining or the people will suffer greatly. Gabrielle has little choice so she agrees. Tataka is reborn. Borshi and his friends find a secret entrance into the palace. They see Tataka but hide. Tataka wants the Gangis river closed off to the people. Its powers threaten her. Queen Tianu sees her sister's favor with Tataka. She grows jealous. Venshue is made Tataka's high priestess. When Tianu objects she is arrested for disobediance. Empress Tataka takes control of the land. She marvels at her improved fighting skills since last time in India. Borshi and his friends try to kidnap her but her powers overcome them. Tataka orders them all with Tianu in prison for beheading. Tianu admits she was wrong to mistreat her people. Borshi and his friends help her to escape and fight the evil Venshue. Venshue is captured and taken away. Borshi's friends surround Tataka and spray her with Gangis water. Gabrielle returns.<br>
      <br>
Season 7, Episode 19<br>
All Roads Lead to Rome<br>
Roman General Sentonius watches his men cut down a forest. Amazons retreat from the area to their camp.  <br>
Gabrielle is approached by an Amazon scout Ersa. Their lands and eventually Potedaia will fall soon. The Amazon Council gives Gabrielle command of the tribes. She travels with Ersa to the Roman camp. Dressed as a merchant, Gabrielle meets Sentonius. He plans to conqueor land from Chin to Gaul to build his roads. Ersa is captured. Gabrielle explains her as a hired guide. Sentonius has his doubts but he lets them leave. Back in the Amazon camp, Gabrielle cautions Ersa on her curiosity. Romans attack the Amazon camp. Gabrielle and the Amazon Queens escape, but Sentonius is later told of many captured Amazons for the slave market. Gabrielle has an idea if the Queens will agree to it. She visits Sentonius as a merchant again. She offers him a harem of ten women for rights to use his roads for trade. Gabrielle is captured. Sentonius learned her true identity. He will still keep the harem girls, but Gabrielle and Ersa are to be taken to Roman court. The harem girls are actually the other Amazon Queens. They attack his guards and a big fight begins. Two of his guards get in Gabrielle's way so Ersa is left to fight Sentonius alone. Gabrielle wins her fight. She throws both sais at Sentonius but he turns slightly. Sentonius and Ersa both fall. The Queens comfort her on her victory but Gabrielle is still sad. <br>
<br>
Season 7, Episode 20<br>
Jihad<br>
Eli, Muhammed and Shiva prophets meet in peace to exchange ideas. Ares appears secretly and uses his powers to make them hate one another. Soon a large battle begins. Days later Gabrielle and Eve see a great battlefield with hundreds of people dead. Eve recognizes fallen friends and runs ahead. Gabrielle knows a war of this greatness is no accident. Ares appears to brag on his greatest challenge, making the followers of peace destroy each other. Eve is furious. She attacks him as strong as when she was Livia. Ares fights back and disappears with a smile. Gabrielle tries to comfort Eve but she will not see Eli's teachings fall. Even if she must attack the other two faiths, Eliasian beliefs must survive. Gabrielle helps the injured. They tell her sometimes the good who are wronged become an even greater threat than the evil. One person mentions an army camp nearby. Gabrielle goes to look. She finds Ares' army quietly waiting. He speaks to his generals of waiting until the three religious armies destroy each other before taking what is left over. Gabrielle is captured. Ares will not let her ruin his plans, but he will let her watch. The next day is a final battle. All three armies meet. Eve leads the Elisians with a war cry but stops when she sees Ares and Gabrielle. Gabrielle pleads with her not to give into hate which is what Ares wants. She listens. Ares' army attacks them all but they loose. Ares is very angry at this loss. He disappears.<br>
<br>
Season 7, Episode 21<br>
Time Stream<br>
Jungle guides bring supplies to research historian Bree. Her tracker Sabine and hired mercenary Brannel stay with her as she activates her time travel creation once again. Somehow Xena's original chakram was found in ancient Central America and Bree intends to find out how. As Brannel goes on patrol, Bree tells Sabine of the cloned Xena and Gabrielle's battles to destroy Alti's research lab. Ever since the government sent soldiers to help Alti and her medical research, they had went into hiding. Sabine had heard rumors of clone Gabrielle's capture and clone Xena's leaving her behind, but Bree disagrees saying that would never happen. Brannel returns with warning of soldiers approaching. They hide. Soon soldiers surround the time machine when clone Xena's battle cry is suddenly heard. As they watch the fight, Bree decides they must help. Sabine leads several guards off into the jungle. Brannel fights with more guards and Bree runs up to clone Xena. A jeep pulls up with Alti and government men. Clone Xena tells Bree they have to escape through the time machine to the past...since Bree is really clone Gabrielle reprogrammed by Alti. Sabine and Brannel are captured. Bree pushes her friend through the time machine but at the last second stays behind to blow up the machine and herself. Alti looses time travel and cloning research. Clone Xena looses her closest friend and the chakram mystery is fullfilled. <br>
<br>
Season 7, Episode 22<br>
Warrior's Return<br>
Medos, a priest of Ares, approaches Gabrielle with Ares' request that she go to his temple. A great warrior will return. Not trusting Ares plan for Xena, Gabrielle agrees to go. Eve is already at the temple when she arrives. Ares tells them both he has found a way to bring Xena back. Gabrielle reminds him she is destined to guard 40,000 souls. Ares says Xena still can but it will take the three of them to bring her back. Eve privately admits it would be nice to see her mother again. Gabrielle agrees but they should be careful. Ares tells Medos to prepare the Summerian soul crystal. Gabrielle and Eve follow Ares to a temple worship room. Ares, Eve and Gabrielle hold hands around the crystal as the chant is made. Xena's soul appears in the crystal along with the 40,000 souls. A vision of Xena warns Gabrielle, but it is too late. Guards capture Eve and Gabrielle. Ares now has an army of lost souls to fight other gods. He continues the chant alone and an image of Xena appears. Even as a spirit Xena will not obey Ares. He tells her to reconsider or Eve and Gabrielle will be harmed. He then tells Eve and Gabrielle if either of them agrees to lead his armies, he will release Xena and her 40,000 souls. Eve says the way of Eli is her only destiny. Gabrielle refuses as well. A powerless Xena yells at Ares to stop as he hurts some of the souls. He doesnt listen. Gabrielle tells him to stop. She closes her eyes and agrees to help Ares. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugabbyshope.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GabbysHOPE</A> at: 5/10/02 10:55:47 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm7.showPrevMessage?topicID=25.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm7.showNextMessage?topicID=25.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=htt